The paper discusses image processing techniques for enhancing the readability of ancient manuscripts, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also evaluates different dimensionality reduction methods, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the methods in high-performance software, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
